t: Amazon Is Selling Terrible Versions of Classic Books. Here's How to Make Sure You Don't Buy One
s: May 8, 2024 - We saw one copy of Moby Dick listed at Amazon at a mere 284 pages, while other editions had over 700 pages. If nothing else, this could mean that you're at risk of buying a book with teeny-tiny type, which might cause more headaches than you'd get trying to decipher the meaning behind Melville's white whale.
